document.title: Audio Lab
document.summary: An experimental toolkit for audio processing prototypes and UI concepts.

body.raw:
## Overview

Audio Lab is where interactive sound concepts are tested before production use.

## Current Work

- Building a small node-based chain editor.
- Prototyping waveform visualizations.
- Experimenting with MIDI routing controls.

```ts
export function normalizeGain(value: number) {
  return Math.min(1, Math.max(0, value));
}
```

document.title: Personal OS
document.summary: A dashboard-style portfolio hub that centralizes projects, quick links, and interactive lab scenes.

body.raw:
## Goals

- Build a polished dashboard interface as a personal home base.
- Keep project information content-driven through MDX and Contentlayer.
- Add lightweight interactive 3D scenes without hurting performance.

> This project acts as a personal operating system, not just a one-page portfolio.

## Highlights

- Multi-page App Router structure with a shared shell.
- Project library with filters for search, tags, and status.
- MDX-driven project detail pages with typed metadata.
- Dedicated lab route with lazy-loaded R3F scenes.

## Notes

Use `npm run dev` to start local development and iterate on content in `content/projects`.
